Develop Attack Trees for Identified Vulnerabilities
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand attack tree methodology and create structured attack trees for system vulnerabilities
Map complex attack paths and chain multiple vulnerabilities together
Develop Python scripts for attack tree generation and analysis
Analyze attack scenarios to prioritize security remediation efforts
Document attack vectors in a structured format for security assessments
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic understanding of cybersecurity concepts and common vulnerabilities (SQL injection, XSS, authentication weaknesses)
Familiarity with Python programming and Linux command line
Knowledge of network security fundamentals and attack vectors
